2:T752,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Kissflow better than Power Automate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"It depends on your needs. Kissflow scores 6.0 overall while Power Automate scores 7.0. Kissflow is best for mid-market companies and process owners, while Power Automate excels for Microsoft 365 users and enterprises."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which is cheaper, Kissflow or Power Automate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Kissflow starts at $1500/mo and Power Automate starts at $15/mo.   Overall value depends on which features you need."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I switch from Kissflow to Power Automate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, most users can migrate between these platforms. Both Kissflow and Power Automate support data import/export. The migration process typically involves exporting your data from one platform and importing it into the other. Some tools also offer migration assistance to make the transition smoother."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What do users say about Kissflow vs Power Automate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"On review platforms, Kissflow holds an overall rating of 6/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10. Power Automate has an overall rating of 7/10 and ease of use score of 6/10. Users praise Kissflow for combines workflow and project management and Power Automate for deep microsoft ecosystem integration."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which should I choose in 2026, Kissflow or Power Automate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"In 2026, we recommend Power Automate for most users based on its overall score and feature set. However, Kissflow remains a strong contender, especially if you prioritize combines workflow and project management. Try both free trials before committing."}}]}0:{"buildId":"oWPZTPCPUwZMl312gxRMA","rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json"